Package it.unive.lisa.analysis.impl.types

Class TypeEnvironment

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.unive.lisa.analysis.BaseLattice<F>
      • it.unive.lisa.analysis.FunctionalLattice<TypeEnvironment,​Identifier,​InferredTypes>
        • it.unive.lisa.analysis.impl.types.TypeEnvironment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Lattice<TypeEnvironment>, SemanticDomain<TypeEnvironment,​ValueExpression,​Identifier>, ValueDomain<TypeEnvironment>, java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Map.Entry<Identifier,​InferredTypes>>
    public final class TypeEnvironment
extends FunctionalLattice<TypeEnvironment,​Identifier,​InferredTypes>
implements ValueDomain<TypeEnvironment>
    A type environment, mapping Identifiers to InferredTypes holding the runtime types of identifiers, that behave the similarly to a ValueEnvironment. The only difference is that smallStepSemantics(ValueExpression) will store the runtime types of the given expression inside the domain, and those will be available through getLastComputedTypes().

        public InferredTypes getLastComputedTypes()

        currentExpression - the expression whose satisfiability is to be evaluated

        public TypeEnvironment lubAux​(TypeEnvironment other)

        Description copied from class: BaseLattice
        Performs the least upper bound operation between this lattice element and the given one, assuming that base cases have already been handled. In particular, it is guaranteed that:

        • other is neither top nor bottom
        • this is neither top nor bottom
        • this and other are not the same object (according both to == and to Object.equals(Object))
